1
00:00:07,478 --> 00:00:09,415
Hello? Hello? Radio Tower?

2
00:00:09,417 --> 00:00:14,136
Lisbon plane taking off
in 10 minutes. East runway. Thank you.

3
00:00:26,256 --> 00:00:29,226
Louis, have your man go with Mr Laszlo
and take care of his luggage.

4
00:00:29,228 --> 00:00:31,311
Certainly, Rick. Anything you say.

5
00:00:31,313 --> 00:00:33,605
Find Mr Laszlo's luggage
and put it on the plane.

6
00:00:33,607 --> 00:00:34,699
Yes, sir.

7
00:00:34,806 --> 00:00:36,151
This way, please.

8
00:00:37,882 --> 00:00:40,353
If you don't mind, you fill in the names.
That'll make it even more official.

9
00:00:40,801 --> 00:00:42,209
You think of everything, don't you?

10
00:00:43,304 --> 00:00:45,952
And the names are
Mr and Mrs Victor Laszlo.

11
00:00:45,994 --> 00:00:49,508
- But... why my name, Richard?
- 'Cause you're getting on that plane.

12
00:00:49,622 --> 00:00:53,157
- I don't understand. What about you?
- I'm staying here with him till the plane gets safely away.

13
00:00:53,167 --> 00:00:55,918
- No, Richard! No, what's happened to you?
Last night you said...

14
00:00:55,920 --> 00:00:57,461
Last night we said a great many things.

15
00:00:57,463 --> 00:00:59,465
You said I was to do the
thinking for both of us.

16
00:00:59,475 --> 00:01:02,362
Well, I've done a lot of it since then and
it all adds up to one thing:

17
00:01:02,364 --> 00:01:04,218
You're getting on that plane
with Victor where you belong.

18
00:01:04,220 --> 00:01:06,764
- But Rick, no I, I...
- Now, you've got to listen to me.

19
00:01:06,805 --> 00:01:10,234
You have any idea what you'd have
to look forward to if you stayed here?

20
00:01:10,236 --> 00:01:14,331
9 chances out of 10 we'd both wind up in a
concentration camp, isn't that true Louis?

21
00:01:14,333 --> 00:01:16,183
I'm afraid Major Strasser would insist.

22
00:01:16,184 --> 00:01:19,588
You're saying this only to make me go.
- I'm saying it because it's true.

23
00:01:19,714 --> 00:01:22,141
Inside of us we both know
you belong with Victor.

24
00:01:22,143 --> 00:01:24,278
You're part of his work,
the thing that keeps him going.

25
00:01:24,280 --> 00:01:27,523
If that plane leaves the ground
and you're not with him, you'll regret it.

26
00:01:27,575 --> 00:01:31,423
Maybe not today, maybe not tomorrow,
but soon for the rest of your life.

27
00:01:32,069 --> 00:01:33,998
But what about us?

28
00:01:34,311 --> 00:01:35,750
We'll always have Paris.

29
00:01:35,812 --> 00:01:39,149
We didn't have we... we'd lost it
until you came to Casablanca.

30
00:01:39,190 --> 00:01:41,586
We got it back last night.

31
00:01:41,860 --> 00:01:45,863
- When I said I would never leave you.
- And you never will.

32
00:01:45,968 --> 00:01:47,563
Look I'm no good at being noble.

33
00:01:47,573 --> 00:01:50,543
But it doesn't take much to see
that the problems of three little people...

34
00:01:50,545 --> 00:01:53,896
don't amount to a hill of beans
in this crazy world.

35
00:01:54,330 --> 00:01:56,975
Someday you'll understand that.

36
00:01:57,958 --> 00:02:00,230
Now, now.

37
00:02:01,378 --> 00:02:03,857
Here's looking at you, kid.

38
00:02:16,288 --> 00:02:18,497
There's something you should
know before you leave.

39
00:02:18,499 --> 00:02:20,686
- Mr. Blaine, I don't ask
you to explain anything.

40
00:02:20,688 --> 00:02:23,647
I'm going to anyway because it may make
a difference to you later on.

41
00:02:23,649 --> 00:02:26,171
You said you know about Ilsa and me.
- Yes.

42
00:02:26,173 --> 00:02:29,132
She didn't know she was at my place
last night when you were.

43
00:02:29,134 --> 00:02:32,366
She came there for the letters of transit.
Isn't that true, Ilsa?

44
00:02:32,887 --> 00:02:34,137
Yes.

45
00:02:34,139 --> 00:02:36,954
She tried everything to get them
but nothing worked.

46
00:02:36,996 --> 00:02:40,395
She did her best to convince me
that she was still in love with me.

47
00:02:40,603 --> 00:02:43,187
But that was all over long ago.

48
00:02:43,238 --> 00:02:47,282
For your sake she pretended it wasn't
and I let her pretend.

49
00:02:47,325 --> 00:02:49,994
- I understand.
- Here it is.

50
00:02:50,036 --> 00:02:52,112
Thanks.

51
00:03:04,967 --> 00:03:07,043
Are you ready, Ilsa?

52
00:03:08,798 --> 00:03:11,053
Yes, I'm ready.

53
00:03:13,239 --> 00:03:15,677
Bye, Rick.

54
00:03:15,679 --> 00:03:18,018
God bless you.

55
00:03:18,814 --> 00:03:21,566
You better hurry,
you'll miss that plane.

56
00:03:50,723 --> 00:03:55,152
It might be a good idea for you to
disappear from Casablanca for a while.

57
00:03:55,154 --> 00:03:59,896
There's a Free French garrison over at Brazzaville.
I could be induced to arrange a passage.

58
00:03:59,898 --> 00:04:03,065
My letter of transit? I could use a trip.

59
00:04:03,107 --> 00:04:06,571
It doesn't make a difference about our bet.
You still owe me 10,000 Francs.

60
00:04:06,665 --> 00:04:09,854
Ah that 10,000 Francs
should pay our expenses.

61
00:04:09,856 --> 00:04:11,887
"Our" expenses?
- Uh huh.

62
00:04:11,889 --> 00:04:16,825
Louis, I think this is the beginning
of a beautiful friendship.

63
00:04:59,369 --> 00:05:02,820
Who am I kidding? I'm not like that.

64
00:05:02,872 --> 00:05:05,577
I never was, I never will be.

65
00:05:06,667 --> 00:05:08,375
That's strictly the movies.

66
00:05:11,380 --> 00:05:13,456
I'm so depressed.

67
00:05:14,842 --> 00:05:18,756
Maybe if I took
two more aspirin it would help.

68
00:05:18,804 --> 00:05:23,015
That would make...
two, four, six aspirin.

69
00:05:24,142 --> 00:05:26,550
I'm turning into an aspirin junkie.

70
00:05:26,603 --> 00:05:31,348
Soon I'll be boiling the cotton
at the top of the bottle to get the extra.

71
00:05:40,992 --> 00:05:43,280
I shouldn't have signed those papers.

72
00:05:43,327 --> 00:05:45,533
Let her take me to court.

73
00:05:45,579 --> 00:05:48,497
Two years of marriage down the drain.

74
00:05:48,541 --> 00:05:51,210
I couldn't believe what she said to me.

75
00:05:51,251 --> 00:05:54,454
She was like a total stranger,
not like my wife.

76
00:05:54,505 --> 00:05:57,956
I don't want any alimony.
I just want out.

77
00:05:58,008 --> 00:06:01,840
- Can't we discuss it?
- We discussed it 50 times.

78
00:06:01,887 --> 00:06:04,342
- Why?
- I don't know.

79
00:06:04,389 --> 00:06:06,465
I can't stand the marriage.

80
00:06:06,516 --> 00:06:08,722
You're no fun, you suffocate me.

81
00:06:08,768 --> 00:06:12,054
There's no rapport
and I don't dig you physically.

82
00:06:12,105 --> 00:06:15,390
For God's sake, Allan,
don't take it personal.

83
00:06:15,441 --> 00:06:18,892
I won't take it personal,
I'll just kill myself.

84
00:06:19,779 --> 00:06:23,194
If only I knew where my analyst
was vacationing.

85
00:06:23,240 --> 00:06:27,534
Where do they go every August?
They leave the city.

86
00:06:27,578 --> 00:06:31,789
Every summer the city is full of people
who are crazy till Labour Day.

87
00:06:31,832 --> 00:06:34,916
What if I reach him?
What's he gonna tell me?

88
00:06:34,960 --> 00:06:38,329
Whatever I say
he tells me it's a sexual problem.

89
00:06:38,380 --> 00:06:41,749
Isn't that ridiculous?
How can it be sexual?

90
00:06:41,800 --> 00:06:44,421
We weren't even having relations.

91
00:06:44,469 --> 00:06:46,545
Maybe once in a while.

92
00:06:46,596 --> 00:06:49,087
She used to watch TV during it.

93
00:06:49,140 --> 00:06:52,425
Change channels
with the remote control.

94
00:06:52,476 --> 00:06:55,561
Why should a divorce bother me so?

95
00:06:55,604 --> 00:06:58,142
Maybe I'm better off without her.

96
00:06:58,190 --> 00:07:01,274
Why not?
I'm young, healthy, got a good job.

97
00:07:01,318 --> 00:07:04,604
This could be my chance
to step out a little bit.

98
00:07:04,655 --> 00:07:06,731
If she can swing, so can l.

99
00:07:06,782 --> 00:07:09,189
I could turn this place into a nightclub.

100
00:07:09,242 --> 00:07:12,243
Get broads here
like you wouldn't believe.

101
00:07:12,287 --> 00:07:14,825
Swingers, freaks, nymphomaniacs,

102
00:07:14,873 --> 00:07:17,198
dental hygienists.

103
00:07:17,250 --> 00:07:20,204
If she didn't want me,
I won't push myself on her.

104
00:07:20,253 --> 00:07:23,538
I couldn't believe
what she said when she left.

105
00:07:23,589 --> 00:07:25,463
I want a new life.

106
00:07:25,508 --> 00:07:28,295
I want to go skiing,
go dancing, go to the beach,

107
00:07:28,344 --> 00:07:30,882
ride through Europe on a motorcycle.

108
00:07:30,930 --> 00:07:34,133
- All we ever do is see movies.
- I write for a film magazine.

109
00:07:34,183 --> 00:07:36,259
Besides, I happen to like movies.

110
00:07:36,310 --> 00:07:40,058
That's because
you're one of life's great watchers.

111
00:07:40,105 --> 00:07:44,814
I'm a doer. I want to participate.
We never laugh together.

112
00:07:44,860 --> 00:07:48,692
How can you say that?
I'm constantly laughing.

113
00:07:48,738 --> 00:07:53,863
I chuckle, I giggle, I guffaw. Why didn't
this come up when we were dating?

114
00:07:53,910 --> 00:07:56,235
You were more aggressive then.

115
00:07:56,287 --> 00:07:59,621
Everybody is during courtship.
It's natural.

116
00:07:59,666 --> 00:08:04,742
You can't expect me to keep up that
level of charm, I'd have a heart attack.

117
00:08:04,795 --> 00:08:07,369
Goodbye, Allan.

118
00:08:07,423 --> 00:08:09,581
My lawyer will call your lawyer.

119
00:08:11,051 --> 00:08:13,127
I don't have a lawyer.

120
00:08:13,178 --> 00:08:15,254
Have him call my doctor.

121
00:08:20,227 --> 00:08:23,512
What's the matter with me?
Why can't I be cool?

122
00:08:23,563 --> 00:08:26,019
What's the secret?

123
00:08:26,066 --> 00:08:30,526
There's no secret, kid.
Dames are simple.

124
00:08:30,570 --> 00:08:34,817
I never met one that didn't understand
a slap in the mouth

125
00:08:34,866 --> 00:08:37,238
or a slug from a .45.

126
00:08:37,285 --> 00:08:39,408
Yeah, cos you're Bogart.

127
00:08:39,453 --> 00:08:42,953
I could never hit Nancy.
It's not that type of relationship.

128
00:08:42,998 --> 00:08:46,248
Where'd you learn that word,
the shrink?

129
00:08:46,293 --> 00:08:51,251
I'm not like you. In Casablanca, when
you lost lngrid, weren't you crushed?

130
00:08:51,298 --> 00:08:54,003
Nothing a little bourbon and soda
wouldn't fix.

131
00:08:54,051 --> 00:08:57,217
I can't drink.
My body won't tolerate alcohol.

132
00:08:57,262 --> 00:09:01,639
Take my advice and forget
all this fancy relationship stuff.

133
00:09:01,683 --> 00:09:03,925
The world is full of dames.

134
00:09:03,977 --> 00:09:06,468
All you got to do is whistle.

135
00:09:13,028 --> 00:09:14,902
He's right.

136
00:09:14,947 --> 00:09:17,817
You give them an inch
and they step all over you.

137
00:09:18,367 --> 00:09:21,237
Why can't I develop that attitude?

138
00:09:21,286 --> 00:09:25,070
Nothing a little bourbon and soda
couldn't fix.

139
00:09:54,276 --> 00:09:56,564
- Are you all right?
- You poor thing!

140
00:09:56,611 --> 00:09:59,648
- Why didn't you call us?
- I didn't want to bother you.

141
00:09:59,698 --> 00:10:03,446
Not bother us?
For God's sake, what are friends for?

142
00:10:03,493 --> 00:10:05,865
Why did she say
she wanted a divorce?

143
00:10:05,912 --> 00:10:08,070
She doesn't laugh enough.

144
00:10:08,122 --> 00:10:11,076
Insufficient laughter -
grounds for divorce.

145
00:10:11,125 --> 00:10:13,201
She wants to go skiing.

146
00:10:13,252 --> 00:10:15,743
She wants to ski
down a mountain laughing.

147
00:10:15,796 --> 00:10:19,960
Let me call my office.
I ran out of a meeting when you called.

148
00:10:20,009 --> 00:10:22,297
They must think I'm crazy.

149
00:10:22,344 --> 00:10:25,879
- Have you heard from her?
- I heard from Schulman and Weiss.

150
00:10:25,931 --> 00:10:29,097
I signed some papers
and Nancy went to Mexico.

151
00:10:29,142 --> 00:10:31,301
We went there on our honeymoon.

152
00:10:31,353 --> 00:10:33,891
Spent the entire two weeks in bed.

153
00:10:33,939 --> 00:10:36,014
I had dysentery.

154
00:10:36,066 --> 00:10:39,648
Hello, George?
Did they agree to the terms?

155
00:10:40,695 --> 00:10:44,230
Oh, hell. Well, if we blow it, we blow it.

156
00:10:44,282 --> 00:10:47,318
God! Can't you cook anything
but TV dinners?

157
00:10:47,368 --> 00:10:50,903
Who bothers to cook them?
I suck them frozen.

158
00:10:50,955 --> 00:10:57,242
I'll tell you where you can reach me,
I'll be at 362-9296 for a while.

159
00:10:57,294 --> 00:11:02,122
Then I'll be at 648-0024
for about 15 minutes.

160
00:11:02,174 --> 00:11:05,377
Then I'll be at 752-0420

161
00:11:05,427 --> 00:11:08,344
and then I'll be home at 621 -4598.

162
00:11:09,097 --> 00:11:10,971
Right, George. Bye-bye.

163
00:11:11,016 --> 00:11:15,060
There's a phone booth on the corner,
shall I get the number?

164
00:11:15,103 --> 00:11:17,558
You'll be passing it.

165
00:11:19,690 --> 00:11:22,976
- I'm sorry, Allan.
- She wants to be a swinger.

166
00:11:23,027 --> 00:11:26,727
- Married life is no good for her.
- Don't get worked up.

167
00:11:26,781 --> 00:11:29,568
I gave her a home, affection, security.

168
00:11:29,617 --> 00:11:33,448
This was a girl I found
waiting on tables at the Hip Bagel.

169
00:11:33,495 --> 00:11:36,366
I used to go there every night
and over-tip her.

170
00:11:36,415 --> 00:11:38,703
$1 .50 on a 35-cent check.

171
00:11:38,750 --> 00:11:41,420
Nancy was impulsive.
We all knew that.

172
00:11:41,461 --> 00:11:45,790
She didn't leave impulsively.
She talked about it for months.

173
00:11:45,840 --> 00:11:49,790
- I didn't believe she'd do it.
- It's good you find out now.

174
00:11:49,844 --> 00:11:53,213
- You're young. Make a new life.
- I'm 29.

175
00:11:53,264 --> 00:11:56,847
The height of my sexual potency
was ten years ago.

176
00:11:56,893 --> 00:11:59,810
Look at the bright side. You're free.

177
00:11:59,854 --> 00:12:01,930
You'll go out, there'll be girls.

178
00:12:01,981 --> 00:12:05,266
You'll go to parties,
have affairs with married women.

179
00:12:05,317 --> 00:12:09,445
Sexual relations with girls
of every race, creed and colour.

180
00:12:10,531 --> 00:12:12,903
You get tired of that.

181
00:12:12,950 --> 00:12:16,034
Besides, those kinds of things
never happen to me.

182
00:12:16,078 --> 00:12:19,992
I managed to fool one girl into
loving me and now she's gone.

183
00:12:20,040 --> 00:12:22,198
See how he downgrades himself?

184
00:12:22,250 --> 00:12:26,200
Don't you think plenty of women
would find him attractive?

185
00:12:26,254 --> 00:12:30,417
- Yes, of course.
- The world's full of eligible women.

186
00:12:30,466 --> 00:12:33,752
Yeah, but not like Nancy.
She was a lovely thing.

187
00:12:33,803 --> 00:12:36,341
I used to lay in bed
and watch her sleep.

188
00:12:36,389 --> 00:12:38,926
Once in a while she'd wake up
and catch me.

189
00:12:38,974 --> 00:12:41,050
She'd let out a scream.

190
00:12:41,101 --> 00:12:44,268
He really loved her. I feel like crying.

191
00:12:44,313 --> 00:12:46,389
Why do you feel like crying?

192
00:12:46,440 --> 00:12:49,606
A man makes an investment,
it doesn't pay off.

193
00:12:49,651 --> 00:12:52,356
Could I get an aspirin?
I have a headache.

194
00:12:52,404 --> 00:12:54,942
He's having a breakdown
and you're sick.

195
00:12:54,990 --> 00:12:59,153
- Don't get upset.
- I'm not, I just had a rough day.

196
00:12:59,202 --> 00:13:02,203
You want an aspirin too?

197
00:13:02,247 --> 00:13:04,951
I ate all the aspirin,
what about Darvon?

198
00:13:04,999 --> 00:13:08,783
Yes, my analyst suggested that
when I have migraines.

199
00:13:08,836 --> 00:13:12,668
I used to get migraines but my analyst
cured me. Now I get cold sores.

200
00:13:12,715 --> 00:13:15,336
I still do. Big, ugly ones from tension.

201
00:13:15,384 --> 00:13:19,678
- I may need a lobotomy.
- With mine away I feel paralysed.

202
00:13:19,722 --> 00:13:22,259
You should move to hospital together.

203
00:13:22,307 --> 00:13:25,807
- You want a Fresca with the Darvon?
- Do you have apple juice?

204
00:13:25,852 --> 00:13:27,762
They're fantastic together.

205
00:13:27,813 --> 00:13:31,016
Have you ever had lithium
and tomato juice?

206
00:13:31,066 --> 00:13:34,481
No, but another neurotic tells me
it's unbelievable.

207
00:13:34,527 --> 00:13:37,445
Can I get a Coke with nothing in it?

208
00:13:39,115 --> 00:13:41,191
I'll get the pills.

209
00:13:44,662 --> 00:13:47,995
Poor guy.
If there's anything we can do...

210
00:13:53,879 --> 00:13:56,370
He never should have married Nancy.

211
00:13:56,423 --> 00:13:58,831
I thought they were getting along.

212
00:13:58,884 --> 00:14:02,928
You're so busy all the time
you never see what's going on.

213
00:14:02,971 --> 00:14:05,676
Didn't you think it strange
that he was married

214
00:14:05,724 --> 00:14:08,428
but still couldn't get a date
on New Year's Eve?

215
00:14:08,476 --> 00:14:10,765
Darling, don't get overwrought.

216
00:14:10,812 --> 00:14:14,975
This is Mr Christie,
I'm no longer at 752-0420,

217
00:14:15,024 --> 00:14:17,978
I'm gonna be home at 621 -4598.

218
00:14:19,070 --> 00:14:21,146
What? Yes, I'll hold on.

219
00:14:21,197 --> 00:14:23,735
Honey, these things upset me.

220
00:14:23,783 --> 00:14:26,902
I'm experiencing a wave of insecurity.

221
00:14:26,952 --> 00:14:30,368
You are? Did I tell you
what happened to me today?

222
00:14:30,414 --> 00:14:32,786
I bought 100 acres of land in Florida

223
00:14:32,833 --> 00:14:35,750
and it turns out that
98 of them have quicksand.

224
00:14:35,794 --> 00:14:38,795
My syndicate wanted to build
a golf course.

225
00:14:38,839 --> 00:14:41,792
All we can do is build
a three-hole golf course

226
00:14:41,841 --> 00:14:44,130
with the biggest sand trap
in the world.

227
00:14:45,804 --> 00:14:48,211
What are you taking a pill for?

228
00:14:48,264 --> 00:14:51,550
- I'm tense.
- Why?

229
00:14:51,601 --> 00:14:56,476
The whole subject of divorce
is traumatic for me.

230
00:14:56,522 --> 00:15:00,733
- He's getting divorced, not us.
- It's the idea of it.

231
00:15:01,819 --> 00:15:05,353
I guess I've never gotten over
my parents' divorce.

232
00:15:05,406 --> 00:15:07,778
Well, it's about time. Come here.

233
00:15:10,912 --> 00:15:14,660
You're so insecure.
I wish I could...

234
00:15:14,707 --> 00:15:17,578
Milt? Dick. That deal is unacceptable.
The figures are lousy.

235
00:15:17,627 --> 00:15:19,418
